# Project: NoteFlow

## Context

Mobile application built with:

* React Native
* Expo
* TypeScript
* Expo Router
* AsyncStorage

Purpose:

Simple note management application using local state and local persistence.

## Architecture

Folders:

app/
components/
hooks/
services/
types/
docs/

## Code Style

* Use TypeScript everywhere.
* Prefer functional components.
* Use React Hooks.
* Avoid class components.
* Use named exports when possible.
* Keep components small and focused.
* Extract reusable logic into hooks.
* Use async/await instead of promise chains.

## State Management

* Use local React state.
* Do not introduce Redux, MobX, Zustand or other state libraries unless explicitly requested.
* Persist data using AsyncStorage.

## UI Rules

* Keep UI simple and minimal.
* Prefer reusable components.
* Avoid inline styles when styles become complex.
* Use StyleSheet.create.

## Naming Conventions

Components: PascalCase

Example:

* NoteCard.tsx
* NoteForm.tsx

Hooks:

* useNotes.ts

Services:

* storage.ts

Types:

* note.ts

## Restrictions

* Do not add unnecessary dependencies.
* Do not introduce backend services.
* Do not add cloud synchronization.
* Do not change folder structure without justification.
* MVP must work fully offline.

## Output Expectations

When generating code:

* Explain architectural decisions briefly.
* Provide complete files.
* Maintain existing project conventions.
* Avoid placeholders whenever possible.
